Devin AI + Delphin AI for EAP Engineering

Purpose: Demonstrate how autonomous AI engineering tools (Devin AI + Delphin AI) can reduce manual effort, increase delivery speed, and safely shrink team size by automating engineering tasks across Cloudera, OpenShift, Ansible, and Terraformâ€”while keeping compliance controls.

1. Executive Summary

This document proposes a controlled pilot of:

Devin AI: an autonomous â€œAI software engineerâ€ that can read repositories, implement changes, run tests, and create pull requests.

Delphin AI: an â€œAI orchestration / agent workflowâ€ tool that routes tickets, applies governance policies, and coordinates multiple AI agents (coding, QA, documentation, compliance checks).

Goal: Reduce engineering toil and ticket cycle time by using AI to perform repeatable engineering tasks and produce PR-ready changes, while humans retain approval/merge and production ownership.

2. Tools Overview
2.1 Devin AI (Autonomous AI Engineer)

What it does

Understands codebase + documentation

Implements changes end-to-end

Runs builds/tests

Iterates based on failures

Produces PRs with explanations

Best fit tasks in EAP

Ansible role creation and refactoring

Terraform module updates

